.TH "clear_nlink" 9 "clear_nlink" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
clear_nlink \- directly zero an inode's link count
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" clear_nlink
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This is a low-level filesystem helper to replace any
direct filesystem manipulation of i_nlink.  See
\fBdrop_nlink\fP for why we care about i_nlink hitting zero.
